HEADWORD: needlebush
<hw>needlebush</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A shrub (<spn>Hakea
lissosperma</spn>) of eastern Australia, with pungent rigid
needle-shaped leaves and white flowers.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> needle bush, <spn>Hakea lissosperma</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
